<module>
    <h>an dé</h>
    <p><g>an dé</g>
        <en>yesterday</en> is an <a href="?xx=prepositions/adverbs">adverb</a>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>Note that <g>an dé</g> is usually spelled with a hyphen and a grave accent, as
                <g>an-dè</g>, in post-1970s writing.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-mod">
            <h>modifier</h>
            <p>Examples modifying <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a> – <ul>
                    <li>past tense – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>An robh Calum ag iasgach air an loch <m>an dé</m>? Bha.</gd>
                                <tr>Was Malcolm fishing on the lake yesterday? Yes, he was.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <gd>An robh an clachair ag obair air a’ bhalla fad an latha <m>an
                                        dé</m>? Bha.</gd>
                                <tr>Was the mason working on the wall all day yesterday? Yes, he
                                    was.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
